## Why Collect It Once

The same physical laws govern all physical domains. Gravity, 
momentum, friction, compliance, impact — these are universal.

A foundation model trained on sufficient real-world inertial 
data across domains develops generalised physical intuition 
that transfers — the same way language models trained on 
diverse text develop generalised language understanding that 
transfers across tasks.

Collecting physical training data per-robot, per-application, 
per-domain is the equivalent of training a new language model 
for every application. Inefficient, inconsistent, never as 
good as the foundation approach.

Collect reality once. Distribute physical intuition universally.

