## Prior Art Statement

To the best of the author's knowledge, no existing AI architecture 
treats real-world inertial experience data as a foundation-layer 
training modality — equivalent in architectural depth to language 
pre-training — with the explicit intent that physical intuition 
be inherited by all downstream models without re-collection.

The distinction between this concept and existing work:
- Not simulation
- Not a physics module
- Not fine-tuning on physical data
- Not per-application data collection

Foundation-level training on real physical experience data, 
collected once, inherited always.

This document establishes the date of conception and sufficient 
technical detail to constitute prior art.

